              Wallmart snapped my lugs off when I bought some studded tires from them.  One of the techs forgot his gun was in the &quot;righty-tighty&quot; position and basically welded 3 of the nuts to the rim.  When they finally came and got me they'd already snapped one off.  At that point they refused to even touch the thing, so I ended up driving it home as it was.  Dad and I spent the next 4 hours heating, beating, and chiseling the nuts and studs out.  Completely ruined the rim in the process.  The new studs popped in in 15 minutes though!<br /><br />I haven't been to Walmart for a tire change since.

              

              
              
