              <div class="quotetitle">coldwave007 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Wallmart snapped my lugs off when I bought some studded tires from them.  One of the techs forgot his gun was in the &quot;righty-tighty&quot; position and basically welded 3 of the nuts to the rim.  When they finally came and got me they'd already snapped one off.  At that point they refused to even touch the thing, so I ended up driving it home as it was.  Dad and I spent the next 4 hours heating, beating, and chiseling the nuts and studs out.  Completely ruined the rim in the process.  The new studs popped in in 15 minutes though!<br /><br />I haven't been to Walmart for a tire change since.</div><br /><br />Did they compensate you in any way? There is no way I would let any mechanic get away with that shit. They might tell me they were not going to deal with it, but they would damned well pay to correct the problem.

              

              
              
